  { question: 'Is virtual staging allowed by MLS rules?', answer: 'Most MLS systems allow virtually staged photos as long as they are clearly labeled as "virtually staged" in the listing description or photo captions. Some MLS systems have specific guidelines about watermarks or disclosure requirements. Always check your local MLS rules before using virtually staged photos, and ensure the staging does not misrepresent the property condition.' },
